   of real numbers.
The square root function 
  
    
      
        f
        (
        x
        )
        =
        
          
            x
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle f(x)={\sqrt {x}}}
   has as its natural domain the set of non-negative real numbers, which can be denoted by 
  
    
      
        
          
            R
          
          
            ≥
            0
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle \mathbb {R} _{\geq 0}}
  , the interval 
  
    
      
        [
        0
        ,
        ∞
        )
      
    
    {\displaystyle [0,\infty )}
  , or 
  
    
      
        {
        x
        ∈
        
          R
        
        :
        x
        ≥
        0
