The tangent function, denoted 
  
    
      
        tan
      
    
    {\displaystyle \tan }
  , has as its natural domain the set of all real numbers which are not of the form 
  
    
      
        
          
            
              π
              2
            
          
        
        +
        k
        π
      
    
